#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/ForceLinkerHeaders.rst:3
msgid "Force-Linker Headers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/ForceLinkerHeaders.rst:5
msgid ""
"The framework is rapidly evolving. The documentation might be out-of-sync "
"with the implementation. The purpose of this documentation is to give "
"context for upcoming reviews."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/ForceLinkerHeaders.rst:10
msgid "The problem"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/ForceLinkerHeaders.rst:12
msgid ""
"SSAF uses `llvm::Registry\\<\\> <https://llvm.org/doxygen/"
"classllvm_1_1Registry.html>`_ for decentralized registration of summary "
"extractors and serialization formats. Each registration is a file-scope "
"static object whose constructor adds an entry to the global registry:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/ForceLinkerHeaders.rst:23
msgid ""
"When the translation unit containing this static object is compiled into a "
"**static library** (``.a`` / ``.lib``), the static linker will only pull in "
"object files that resolve an undefined symbol in the consuming binary. "
"Because no code ever calls anything in ``MyExtractor.o`` directly, the "
"linker discards the object file — and the registration never runs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/ForceLinkerHeaders.rst:29
msgid ""
"This is not a problem for **shared libraries** (``.so`` / ``.dylib``), "
"because the dynamic linker loads the entire shared object and runs all "
"global constructors unconditionally."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/ForceLinkerHeaders.rst:34
msgid "The solution: anchor symbols"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/ForceLinkerHeaders.rst:36
msgid ""
"Each registration translation unit defines a ``volatile int`` **anchor "
"symbol**:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/ForceLinkerHeaders.rst:44
msgid ""
"A **force-linker header** declares the symbol as ``extern`` and reads it "
"into a ``[[maybe_unused]] static int`` destination:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/ForceLinkerHeaders.rst:54
msgid ""
"Any translation unit that ``#include``\\s this header now has a reference to "
"``SSAFMyExtractorAnchorSource``, which forces the linker to pull in "
"``MyExtractor.o`` — and with it, the static ``Add<>`` registration object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/ForceLinkerHeaders.rst:58
msgid ""
"The ``volatile`` qualifier is essential: without it the compiler could "
"constant-fold the ``0`` and eliminate the reference entirely."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/ForceLinkerHeaders.rst:62
msgid "Header hierarchy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/ForceLinkerHeaders.rst:69
msgid ""
"``clang/include/clang/ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/SSAFBuiltinForceLinker."
"h`` — anchors for upstream-provided (built-in) extractors and formats (e.g. "
"``JSONFormat``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/ForceLinkerHeaders.rst:71
msgid ""
"``clang/include/clang/ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/SSAFForceLinker.h`` — "
"umbrella header that includes ``SSAFBuiltinForceLinker.h``.  This is the "
"header that downstream projects should modify to add their own force-linker "
"includes (see :doc:`HowToExtend`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/ForceLinkerHeaders.rst:76
msgid ""
"Include the umbrella header with ``// IWYU pragma: keep`` in any translation "
"unit that must guarantee all registrations are active — typically the entry "
"point of a binary that uses ``clangScalableStaticAnalysisFrameworkCore``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/ForceLinkerHeaders.rst:86
msgid "Naming convention"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/ForceLinkerHeaders.rst:88
msgid ""
"Anchor symbols follow the pattern ``SSAF<Component>AnchorSource`` and "
"``SSAF<Component>AnchorDestination``.  For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/ForceLinkerHeaders.rst:91
msgid "``SSAFJSONFormatAnchorSource`` / ``SSAFJSONFormatAnchorDestination``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/ForceLinkerHeaders.rst:92
msgid "``SSAFMyExtractorAnchorSource`` / ``SSAFMyExtractorAnchorDestination``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/ForceLinkerHeaders.rst:95
msgid "Considered alternatives"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/ForceLinkerHeaders.rst:98
msgid "``--whole-archive`` / ``-force_load``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/ForceLinkerHeaders.rst:100
msgid ""
"The linker can be instructed to include *every* object file from a static "
"library, regardless of whether any symbols are referenced:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/ForceLinkerHeaders.rst:111
msgid ""
"Since CMake 3.24, the ``$<LINK_LIBRARY:WHOLE_ARCHIVE,...>`` generator "
"expression provides a portable way to do the same:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/ForceLinkerHeaders.rst:119
#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/ForceLinkerHeaders.rst:143
msgid "**Why we did not choose this approach**:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/ForceLinkerHeaders.rst:121
msgid ""
"It is a blunt instrument — *all* object files in the library are pulled in, "
"increasing binary size."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/ForceLinkerHeaders.rst:123
msgid ""
"The anchor approach only targets specific object files: only registrations "
"whose anchors are referenced in a force-linker header are pulled in."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/ForceLinkerHeaders.rst:125
msgid ""
"``--whole-archive`` semantics vary across platforms and toolchains, "
"requiring platform-specific CMake logic or the relatively new "
"``WHOLE_ARCHIVE`` generator expression."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/ForceLinkerHeaders.rst:130
msgid "Explicit initialization functions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/ForceLinkerHeaders.rst:132
msgid ""
"An alternative is a central ``initializeSSAFRegistrations()`` function that "
"explicitly calls into each registration module:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/ForceLinkerHeaders.rst:145
msgid ""
"It reintroduces a centralized list that must be maintained manually, "
"defeating the decoupled-registration benefit of ``llvm::Registry``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/ForceLinkerHeaders.rst:147
msgid ""
"Adding a new extractor or format requires modifying a central file, which "
"increases merge-conflict risk for downstream users."
msgstr ""
